🛡️ Scam RAG Detector

An AI-powered scam detection assistant built using Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG).

Paste any suspicious message and the system performs semantic search + LLM reasoning to determine if it looks like a scam.

🚀 Example

Input message:

Congratulations! You've won a $1000 gift card. Click here to claim before it expires!

Output:

Is this a scam? YES
Risk Level: HIGH

Reason:
Uses urgency tactics and unrealistic rewards — common phishing patterns.

🧠 How The System Works
spam.txt → ingest.py → FAISS vector database
                               ↓
User message → similarity search → LLM analysis → risk report

Step 1 — Ingest

ingest.py loads known scam messages and converts them into embeddings.

These embeddings are stored inside a FAISS vector database.

Step 2 — Retrieve

When a user pastes a new message, the system finds the most similar scam patterns from the database.

Step 3 — Analyze

An LLM analyzes the message against those patterns and produces a human-readable risk explanation.

📁 Project Structure
Scam RAG/
│
├── app.py
├── rag.py
├── ingest.py
├── spam.txt
│
├── vector_db/
│
├── requirements.txt
├── .env
└── .gitignore

File descriptions

app.py

Streamlit interface where users paste suspicious messages.

rag.py

Handles retrieval + LLM reasoning.

ingest.py

Reads the dataset and builds the FAISS vector database.

spam.txt

Dataset of labeled SMS messages.

vector_db/

Automatically created after running ingest.py.

.env

Stores API keys.

⚙️ Setup
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/ShazaMumtaz20/scam-rag-detector.git
cd scam-rag-detector

2. Create a virtual environment
python -m venv venv


Activate it:

Windows
venv\Scripts\activate

Mac / Linux
source venv/bin/activate

3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Add your Groq API key

Get a free key from:

https://console.groq.com

Create a .env file:

GROQ_API_KEY=your-key-here

5. Build the vector database

Run:

python ingest.py


This creates the FAISS vector database inside vector_db/.

6. Run the application
streamlit run app.py


Open in browser:

http://localhost:8501

🧰 Tech Stack
Tool	Purpose
Streamlit	Web interface
FAISS	Vector similarity search
sentence-transformers	Embedding model
langchain-huggingface	Embedding integration
langchain-community	FAISS integration
langchain-text-splitters	Text chunking
Groq	LLM inference
📄 Dataset Format

The dataset is tab-separated:

ham    Hey, are you free tomorrow?
spam   You have been selected for a FREE iPhone. Claim now!


Only spam rows are indexed in the vector database.

⚠️ Important Notes

.env and vector_db/ are not pushed to GitHub

Run ingest.py locally to regenerate the vector database

Embeddings run locally for free

Only the LLM call uses the Groq API

